      • loadClassInstance

        public java.lang.Object loadClassInstance​(java.lang.String className,
                                          MultiTreeMap creationData,
                                          boolean splitArguments)
                                   throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException,
                                          java.lang.InstantiationException,
                                          java.lang.NoSuchMethodException,
                                          java.lang.IllegalAccessException,
                                          java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
        Specified by:
        loadClassInstance in interface ClassFactory
        Parameters:
        className - - classpath for the class to load.
        creationData - - data to use for creating the new instance. This may be null.
        splitArguments - - if true, all first values of simple keys from creationData are passed individually to the constructor. If splitArguments is true and creationData is null, the constructor will be called with no arguments.
        Returns:
        a new instance for the class.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - if the class was not found.
        java.lang.InstantiationException - if the class could not be instantiated.
        java.lang.NoSuchMethodException - if an adequate constructor was not found.
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - if the constructor is not accessible.
        java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - if the constructor could not be invoked.
